		<div class="accordion-item mb-5">
			<div class="accordion-header" id="fact-header">
				<h2 class="primary-header-text-color"><button disabled class="accordion-button primary-header-text-color"
						type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#fact-collapse" aria-expanded="false"
						aria-controls="fact-collapse">Some Tiktok Tips and Facts</button></h2>
			</div>
			<div id="fact-collapse" class="fact-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="fact-header"
				data-bs-parent="#accordion">
				<div class="accordion-body">
					<div class="row text-left">
						<h3>Putting a thumbnail to your video will attract more people to watch it</h3>
						<p>As we have explained in previous section. A good thumbnail would make your video stand out in a search result. It also makes all the videos in your profile easier to manage since you can tell what it's about by looking at the thumbnail.</p>
						<h3>The first 3 seconds are crucial! Grab attention with a question, surprising fact, funny skit, or intriguing visuals</h3>
						<p>Putting a random template such as the water flowing or sunset before playing the actual video would boost it because the score of total watch time for that video is high and it's more likely to be recommended to other users. This approach could be combined with tikthumb to create seamless experience for the owner and the viewers. Using the default video thumbnail that the platform creates for you would be bad for search result and video management.</p>
						<h3>Trendy sounds and hashtags are your friends! They expose your video to a wider audience riding a wave of popularity.</h3>
						<p>Search trending sounds and hashtags related to your niche. Don't overload on hashtags, but use a relevant mix.</p>
						<h3>People love to feel heard! Respond to comments, answer questions, and stitch replies to build a community.</h3>
						<p>Ask questions at the end of your video to spark conversation. Run polls or challenges to get people involved.</p>
						<h3>There are peak times for posting depending on your audience. Research the best time to reach them.</h3>
						<p>Analyze your video insights to see when you get the most engagement. Schedule posts for optimal visibility</p>
						<h3>Short and sweet is key! Most popular videos are under one minute long</h3>
						<p>By following these tips and fun facts, you can create engaging TikToks that will have viewers hitting that like button and coming back for more!</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="accordion-item mb-5">
			<div class="accordion-header" id="contact-header">
